title: 4 city inspectors slain at Mexico's Playa del Carmen resort
description: Four tortured bodies were found stuffed into a vehicle.

title: High-altitude object shot down over northern Canada
description: A high-altitude object was tracked over northern Canada, the North American Aerospace Defense Command said Saturday.

title: Texas dad convicted of murder in fatal shootings by teen son
description: A Texas man has been convicted of capital murder in the fatal shooting of three teenagers by the man's then-14-year-old son

title: Flint residents under citywide boil water advisory after water main break
description: Flint announced a citywide boil water advisory after a water main broke Friday morning, causing the pressure of the entire city's system to drop below safe levels.

title: Fuel pipeline leak prompts state of emergency from Nevada governor
description: Nevada Gov. Joe Lombardo declared a state of emergency as the state prepares for shortages caused by a fuel pipeline leak in California.

title: US blacklists 6 Chinese entities over balloon program
description: The United States has blacklisted six Chinese entities it says are linked to Beijing’s aerospace programs as part of its retaliation over an alleged Chinese spy balloon that traversed U.S. airspace

title: Biden Super Bowl interview appears off after back-and-forth between Fox, White House
description: A White House spokesperson said Fox's statement that the interview with President Biden was back on was "inaccurate."

title: Migrants seeking US sponsors find questionable offers online
description: An underground market has emerged for migrants seeking U.S. sponsors since the Biden administration announced last month that it would accept a limited number of people from Venezuela, Cuba, Nicaragua and Haiti

title: Plane-bus collide at LA airport, sending 4 to the hospital
description: A jet being towed on a taxiway collided with a bus at Los Angeles International Airport, injuring five people

title: East Germany's last communist leader dies at 95
description: Hans Modrow, who served as East Germany’s last communist leader during a turbulent tenure that ended in the country’s first and only free election, has died

title: Wagner owner says war in Ukraine will drag on for years
description: The owner of the Russian Wagner Group private military contractor actively involved in the fighting in Ukraine has predicted that the war could drag on for years

title: Hilltop coal-mining town a tactical prize in Ukraine war
description: The small coal-mining town of Vuhledar on Ukraine's eastern front line has emerged as a critical hot spot in the fight for Donetsk province

title: At least 26 dead and 2,000 injured as wildfires rage out of control across Chile
description: Wildfires that have been raging across Chile for more than a week have now killed at least 26 people and left more than 2,000 injured.

title: New Mexico St. suspends operations of men's basketball team
description: New Mexico State has suspended operations of its men’s basketball program placed its coaching staff on paid administrative leave due to allegations unrelated to a fatal shooting last year

title: Toronto mayor steps down after affair with ex-staffer
description: The mayor of Canada’s largest city has stepped down after after acknowledging he had an affair with a former staffer

title: Fuel lines from Los Angeles to Vegas, Phoenix shut by leak
description: A leak in a fuel pipeline facility in California has forced a shutdown of deliveries of gasoline and diesel from the Los Angeles to areas including Las Vegas and Phoenix

title: WATCH:  The woman behind historic Super Bowl mural art
description: ABC News’ Kayna Whitworth spoke with Lucinda “La Morena” Hinojos, the first Chicana Indigenous woman to be named marquee artist for the Super Bowl.

title: Police release footage in arrest of man who died after being tased 3 times
description: Police in North Carolina have released body-worn camera and surveillance footage showing the arrest of Darryl Tyree Williams, who died after being tased three times.

title: Balenciaga's creative director Demna speaks out for the first time amid BDSM scandal
description: Balenciaga's creative director Demna Gvasalia opened up for the first time to Vogue about the brand's BDSM scandal calling it a "big mistake."

title: Attorney who helped Santos fight bad check charges now thinks he wasn't innocent
description: An attorney friend of embattled Rep. George Santos who helped him fight charges that he wrote several bad checks in 2017 now says she no longer believes he was innocent.

title: Multiple people injured in shooting in Southern California
description: Multiple people were injured in a shooting in Southern California on Friday, authorities said.

title: Investigators subpoena American Airlines crew involved in near-miss at JFK airport
description: U.S. investigators have subpoenaed the American Airlines crew involved in a near-miss earlier this year after they "refused" to be interviewed on tape.

title: CSX railroad promises paid sick time to two more unions
description: CSX railroad has promised to give more of its workers the paid sick time they demanded in contract negotiations last fall

title: Tests negative, Sen. John Fetterman leaves hospital
description: Pennsylvania Democratic Sen. John Fetterman is out of a hospital in Washington after a two-day stay following a spell of lightheadedness that prompted the visit as he recovers from a stroke he suffered last year on the campaign trail
